                    Specifies the sampler to which the texture from which texels will be retrieved is bound.
                </p></dd><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>P</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the texture coordinates at which texture will be sampled.
                </p></dd><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>lod</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the explicit level-of-detail
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="description"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">textureLod</code> performs a texture lookup at coordinate <em class="parameter"><code>P</code></em> from the
            texture bound to <em class="parameter"><code>sampler</code></em> with an explicit level-of-detail as specified in <em class="parameter"><code>lod</code></em>.
            <em class="parameter"><code>lod</code></em> specifies
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:msub><mml:mi>λ</mml:mi><mml:mi>base</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math>
            and sets the partial derivatives as follows:
        </p><p>
